  "research_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">The <strong>Epigrams</strong> of Demodocus of Leros constitute a collection of short, gnomic verses belonging to the archaic Greek tradition of invective and wisdom poetry. Preserved as twelve fragments, primarily within the fifth-century CE anthology compiled by Stobaeus, these are self-contained, cynical maxims concerning human nature and social conduct rather than formal dedicatory inscriptions. The tenth-century Byzantine encyclopedia, the <strong>Suda</strong>, describes his work as poems full of censure. The surviving fragments offer pithy, often misanthropic advice and critique, expressing a deep skepticism toward friendship and human trust, observations on the instability of fortune, and authoritative, moralizing statements on ethics and social behavior. The work survives only indirectly through quotation by later anthologists, chiefly Stobaeus, and is referenced in the <strong>Suda</strong>, with no independent manuscript tradition. Demodocus is counted among canonical gnomic poets such as Theognis and Phocylides. His proverbial, censorious verses contributed to the broader tradition of Greek wisdom literature, and their preservation by Stobaeus confirms their continued value as sententious material for later Greek readers.</p>\n</div>",
  "rows": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 235.1.1",
      "text": "Καὶ τόδε Δημοδόκου· Χῖοι κακοί, οὐχ ὁ μέν, ὃς δ’ οὔ,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 235.1.2",
      "text": "πάντες, πλὴν Προκλέους· καὶ Προκλέης δὲ Χίος.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 236.1.1",
      "text": "Πάντες μὲν Κίλικες κακοὶ ἀνέρες· ἐν δὲ Κίλιξιν",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 236.1.2",
      "text": "εἷς ἀγαθὸς Κινύρης, καὶ Κινύρης δὲ Κίλιξ.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 237.1.1",
      "text": "Καππαδόκην ποτ’ ἔχιδνα κακὴ δάκεν, ἀλλὰ καὶ αὐτὴ",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 237.1.2",
      "text": "κάτθανε γευσαμένη αἵματος ἰοβόλου.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 238.1.1",
      "text": "Καππαδόκαι φαῦλοι μὲν ἀεί, ζώνης δὲ τυχόντες",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 238.1.2",
      "text": "φαυλότεροι, κέρδους δ’ εἵνεκα φαυλότατοι.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 238.1.3",
      "text": "ἢν δ’ ἄρα δὶς καὶ τρὶς μεγάλης δράξωνται ἀπήνης,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 238.1.4",
      "text": "δὴ τότε γίνονται φαυλεπιφαυλότατοι.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 238.5",
      "text": "μή, λίτομαι, βασιλεῦ, μὴ τετράκις, ὄφρα μὴ αὐτὸς",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 238",
      "text": "κόσμος ὀλισθήσῃ καππαδοκιζόμενος.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    }
  ],
